{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4c582519-6bd1-4deb-a618-3c2c813f1a37","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update the adapter** — upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it includes Microsoft.Testing.Platform support).\n\n2. **Remove** the `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package reference — it's no longer needed.\n\n3. **Add the MSBuild property** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or run the test executable directly (it's now a standalone app).\n\n**Optional but recommended:** Add `<EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>` if you need code coverage, and `<TestingExtensionsTrxReport>true</TestingExtensionsTrxReport>` for TRX reports — these were previously bundled with `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` but are now opt-in.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5714c4de-91fb-46f0-86cd-32d2edd6328b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question — I don't need to look at any files. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":340},"id":"b0383850-ea83-49c5-b25c-0b3364408afa","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:20:53.199Z","parentId":"08cf972c-7934-482f-b8c2-5938d37596b4"}
